div1.p: United States District Court Western District of Washington Northern Division
In the Matter of the Application of Ching Hing for a Writ of Habeas Corpus } No. 2875
U.S. Immigration Service Recieved APR 3 1915 Seattle, Wash. 9:50 AM
The United States of America Western District of Washington Northern Division }ss.

Henry M. White, being first duly sworn on oath, deposes and says: That he is Commissioner of Immigration at Seattle, Washington, and that the attached bill in favor of J. Richard Lane, Esq., is a just bill for the board of the petitioner herein from September 29, 2914 to March 4, 1915, as therein specified and that they money now on deposit in the Registry of the Court for the payment of the board of said petitioner should be applied on said bill.
div1.ab: Henry M. White Commissioner of Immigration.
div1.p: Subscribed and sworn to before me this 3rd day of April, 1915.
div1.ab: John H. Sargent Notary Public and for the State of Washington, residing in Seattle
div1.p: Mr. John J. sullivan, L.C. Smith Building, Seattle
To J. Richard Lane Dr. 644 Central Building
For meals furnished at U.S. Immigration Station, Seattle, during the month of as follows:
Ching Hing ex S.S. Protesilaus August 5, 1914. From September 29 after Supper To February 28 after Supper 456 meals @ 20¢ each, $91.20
From Feb 28 after supper To Mar 4 after dinner 11 meals @ 20¢ 2.20
Apr. 3 1915 OK Henry A. Mainor Just
In the District Court of the United States for the Western District of Washington. Northern Divison. G0B-5-274
In the Matter of the Application of Ching Hing for a Writ of Habeas Corpus.
Filed in the U.S. District Court, Western Dist. of Washington Northern Division APR 5 1915 Frank L. Crosby, Clerk. By EML Deputy
